Just to make sure

  1. On your default gateway site, for ip you put your ip addressv4 from start>run>cmd>ipconfig right?
  2. You opened port through firewall
  3. Open no-ip while other ppl are trying to log on?
  4. Firewall has to be off
  5. Runserver on of course
  6. if you have linksys, 95% it is wireless, that means you have to use a laptop
  7. Have to setup static ip so every time you have your no-ip DUC on, it doesn’t change your ip
